<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>I wish I could openly comment on what I will be.. I'll just say, Ill be evil :) (nt)</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Tarquin">Tarquin</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 1:47 a.m. 15/3/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> I wish I could openly comment on what I will be.. I'll just say, Ill be evil :) (nt)<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=1395" TARGET=_self>Warrior vs Spellcaster on PvP</A> (Madman at Large)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>> Was afraid that the PvP server was going to be flooded with

<BR>&gt; juveniles, but, to my suprise in general the players where
<BR>&gt; mature and civil. Beacause of the limited time I got on the
<BR>&gt; server I didn't get to experiment with that many different
<BR>&gt; classes in player vs. player combat. Let's talk in the limited
<BR>&gt; scope of 1 vs. 1. Isn't root essential? Damn if I didn't have a
<BR>&gt; hell of a time running little backstabbers down with my shadow
<BR>&gt; knight! It seems that spellcasting is essential for successfull
<BR>&gt; PvP combat. Please share with me your experiences, and, if you
<BR>&gt; dont mind, your race/class choice for the final.
<P>&gt; My current thoughts are:
<BR>&gt; 1. HUMAN NECROMANCER
<BR>&gt; 2. HALF-ELF RANGER ( QUICK ADVANCEMENT FROM TRACKING)
<BR>&gt; 3. HUMAN MONK (EASY TO BOUNCE BACK FROM A BAD FIGHT)
<BR>&gt; 4. TROLL SHAMAN (ROOT)
<BR>&gt; 5. EURODITE WIZARD
<P>&gt; Are dark-elves viable to travel the world with? Will my friends
<BR>&gt; be constantly groaning over taking the long route? Do
<BR>&gt; RANGER/PALIDIN/SHADOW-KNIGHTS ever get higher than 3rd circle
<BR>&gt; spells? Do any get bind? What are YOU going to play, and WHY?
<BR>
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
